Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are waiting for the moment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The words we exchange\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and a chance meeting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}People, no matter who they are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}As we leave behind a living\N{\c&He1e1e1&}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways on which\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.19,0:01:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Long ago, there was a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}war on a faraway planet.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.53,0:01:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}A pitch-black train appeared,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and took the dead aboard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.87,0:01:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}When there was a terrible\N{\c&He1e1e1&}accident on the Orion Line,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.87,0:02:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and when epidemics would break out,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.81,0:02:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}the pitch-black train appeared, and would\N{\c&He1e1e1&}take aboard a large number of deceased.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Those Who Call Themselves Eternal"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.17,0:02:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother, where do you think\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you're going!? Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.17,0:02:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen is no longer around.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}What good will it do to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's no way a ghost train\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is coming here, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.18,0:02:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even if it's only for just a glance,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I want to see Karen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.52,0:02:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Jane, you go on home already!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.52,0:02:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No way! If you're going to stay\N{\c&He1e1e1&}here, Brother, then I'm staying too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.53,0:02:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Suit yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How could you leave your camera behind,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}after taking such good care of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.47,0:03:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aren't you planning on coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.81,0:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You said you were going to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}take the kinds of pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.51,0:03:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that would give the people\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of the world happy memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Jane...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.15,0:03:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I shouldn't have yelled at you. But\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this is the only way I can see Karen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.49,0:03:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You have to understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.82,0:03:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The planet Meridies goes around two\N{\c&He1e1e1&}different suns, in a figure-8 pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.50,0:03:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It is a daytime planet, without night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.16,0:03:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}However, due to its orbit,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}there is one night that comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.77,0:03:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but that night only\N{\c&He1e1e1&}lasts for ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.17,0:03:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The ghost train will come at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.85,0:03:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.19,0:03:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.14,0:04:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother, don't go! Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.14,0:04:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.17,0:04:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.94,0:04:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you know that story about the ghost\N{\c&He1e1e1&}train that runs on the Orion Line?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.28,0:04:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:04:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's a special train, that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}takes you to the spirit world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.48,0:05:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once you board it, it's the end\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for you. You'll never come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.55,0:05:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}In the middle of the night, a pitch-black\N{\c&He1e1e1&}train silently comes to a stop
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.89,0:05:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}at the platform, and a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}white hand beckons you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.55,0:05:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Come here, come here..."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.23,0:05:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you spacing off about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.90,0:05:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No way, Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}, are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.24,0:05:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not really. I just heard the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.90,0:05:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even so, do you think it's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}okay for a member of the SDF
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.27,0:05:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}to be talking about ghost trains?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.58,0:05:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not me, I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.24,0:05:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, you're the one who likes\N{\c&He1e1e1&}those kinds of stories, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.91,0:05:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Me? No way, you must be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.25,0:05:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I'll just bet she likes{\i0}\N{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}them, all right...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.59,0:05:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Members of Sirius Platoon, please\N{\c&He1e1e1&}assemble in the briefing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.26,0:05:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Members of Sirius Platoon, please\N{\c&He1e1e1&}assemble in the briefing room.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Uh-oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.93,0:05:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.27,0:05:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm coming, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.60,0:05:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.94,0:05:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.87,0:06:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}According to what an eyewitness said,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.54,0:06:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the train in question had a pitch-black\N{\c&He1e1e1&}body, and double headlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.88,0:06:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Its model number is unknown, but\N{\c&He1e1e1&}it resembled Production No. 138,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.75,0:06:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}a train that was suspended\N{\c&He1e1e1&}during the development stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.89,0:06:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The missing person is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Terry Goldman, age 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Three months ago, he\N{\c&He1e1e1&}got aboard this train
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.83,0:06:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}at the abandoned Alpha Centauri\N{\c&He1e1e1&}platform, and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.56,0:06:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our mission is to search for Terry,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.57,0:06:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}as well as to investigate this\N{\c&He1e1e1&}suspicious train. Any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is he talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.24,0:06:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Weren't you listening?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}It's that story you just told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Has this unknown train\N{\c&He1e1e1&}appeared anywhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.24,0:06:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}According to reports, the Orion\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Line, the Aldebaran Loop,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.15,0:06:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the Alpha Centauri Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why hasn't anyone done\N{\c&He1e1e1&}anything for three months?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Because night only comes once\N{\c&He1e1e1&}every three months there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Apparently, the train\N{\c&He1e1e1&}only appears at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.60,0:06:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's a ghost train, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.60,0:06:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who was the witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.93,0:07:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Jane Goldman, age 19. She is the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}sister of the missing person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.20,0:07:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She's the only one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.54,0:07:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.54,0:07:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That woman is suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.54,0:07:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.88,0:07:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He boarded a ghost\N{\c&He1e1e1&}train and went missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.64,0:07:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sure we'll find his body around\N{\c&He1e1e1&}there someplace, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.21,0:07:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You can't mean that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.21,0:07:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You really are a patsy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.22,0:07:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay then, everyone to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your stations. Dismissed!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.56,0:07:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.56,0:07:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be late. Got that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.90,0:07:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's go, kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}System check, standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.24,0:07:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0} moving to launch position.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.57,0:07:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ascent Float lock confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.24,0:07:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Gravitational barrier\N{\c&He1e1e1&}generator systems normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.58,0:07:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Energy normal. Pressure within the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}boiler is rising. Cylinder valves open.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.92,0:07:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engage main circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.25,0:07:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.92,0:07:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Systems all green!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.26,0:08:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0}, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.22,0:08:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}A ghost train, huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.23,0:08:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}That's crazy!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.56,0:08:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.23,0:08:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Train-sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.23,0:08:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, could you at least put\N{\c&He1e1e1&}away your own dirty dishes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.24,0:08:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, I'm sorry. I have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a habit of doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.24,0:08:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's one nasty habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.24,0:08:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You hush up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.20,0:09:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This sure is an awful place, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This station was put out of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}use twenty years ago, and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.54,0:09:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}According to calculations, it's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}five minutes and eleven seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}until the time when that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}train is supposed to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.21,0:09:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What calculations are those?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.88,0:09:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I took witness' story and figured\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the number of days that have passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.62,0:09:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and then corrected for the orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.22,0:09:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Want to put money on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.22,0:09:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.22,0:09:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How much do you think\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you can get out of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.89,0:09:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}These are all trampled,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and I can't make much of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.29,0:09:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And it's hard to ask around on\N{\c&He1e1e1&}an uninhabited planet, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.23,0:09:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I wonder what that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Infinity?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.90,0:09:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Unlimited. Eternal. That kind of scope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.57,0:09:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's what my brother drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.91,0:10:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Jane Goldman!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You're Terry's sister, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.55,0:10:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why did your brother get on that train?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.25,0:10:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.58,0:10:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.27,0:10:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, no! It's going to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}collide with {\i1}Big One{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.28,0:10:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.62,0:10:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop her! It's too dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.29,0:10:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Jane-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.96,0:10:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki! Louis! Hold up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.63,0:10:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I- it vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.93,0:11:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}H- hey there...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get up, would you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.27,0:11:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're so heavy, I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What do you mean, heavy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.61,0:11:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yowch...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.28,0:11:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop sticking on me! I can't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.28,0:11:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That goes double for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.62,0:11:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is this? How is this a ghost train?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.95,0:11:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Um, where is it you're heading?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.62,0:11:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This train has no last stop.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You decide for yourself when you get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.96,0:11:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You can ride forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.30,0:11:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.97,0:12:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We don't want to get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.57,0:12:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We still want to watch the world we\N{\c&He1e1e1&}were in for a little while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.91,0:12:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're looking for this person.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Have you seen him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.24,0:12:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not sure. Perhaps he got on,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}perhaps he didn't. I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.25,0:12:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Next stop,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Hazama ("In-between") Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.62,0:12:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We will stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.25,0:12:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...for 18 minutes and 30 seconds.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Louis, let's go check out\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the conductor's compartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.59,0:12:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.59,0:12:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You may not come in here.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}This is the conductor's compartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I am Yuuki Manabu, of Sirius Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is this train's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}identification number?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.94,0:12:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It has no identification number.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.60,0:12:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What about a destination?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our next stop is Hazama Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.27,0:12:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's not what I meant. I want to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}know where it is you're heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.28,0:12:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We have no specific destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.28,0:12:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What kind of train is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.62,0:12:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I do not understand your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.95,0:12:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's no use, Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}. He can't answer\N{\c&He1e1e1&}any questions he isn't programmed for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's look for Terry, instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.29,0:12:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.23,0:13:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.91,0:13:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.91,0:13:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.91,0:13:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're Karen, aren't you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.25,0:13:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sir, would you like some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.25,0:13:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.92,0:13:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've come at last, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen! Where have you been up to now!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.92,0:13:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You fool. Why have you come\N{\c&He1e1e1&}all the way to this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.59,0:13:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I missed you. No matter what,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I wanted to see you once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.60,0:13:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why? I am no longer of this world.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}What good will it do to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.27,0:13:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen! Don't say that.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Why would you say such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.28,0:13:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I haven't been able to sleep since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.28,0:13:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Your voice... your figure...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}they've been burned into me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.28,0:13:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and I cannot shake you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.95,0:13:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay, I'll see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.29,0:13:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.89,0:14:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.56,0:14:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.56,0:14:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Next Sunday...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.13,0:14:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.89,0:14:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're coming, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.23,0:14:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.90,0:14:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Be sure you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.23,0:14:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll be sure to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.90,0:14:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.58,0:14:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Terry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.58,0:14:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's something I wanted to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}tell you. But in your condition...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.26,0:14:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.59,0:14:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please, don't go anywhere again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.60,0:14:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry, Terry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.94,0:14:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I was afraid to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.61,0:15:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But if I got off, we could\N{\c&He1e1e1&}never see each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.28,0:15:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay. I knew, Karen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.22,0:15:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Terry-{\i1}san{\i0}, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.22,0:15:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We are members of the SDF. There was\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a request made to search for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.56,0:15:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you guys alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.90,0:15:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You guys are alive, right? Go on back!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}This train is for the deceased!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.57,0:15:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're alive too, and we\N{\c&He1e1e1&}came to take you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.24,0:15:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Terry-{\i1}san{\i0}, your sister\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.58,0:15:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Terry?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.58,0:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Louis Fort Drake. We found\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Terry. Captain? Captain Bulge?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.59,0:15:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not getting through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.25,0:15:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Yuuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.59,0:15:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- It couldn't be!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.59,0:15:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Time has stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.60,0:15:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those rookies {\i1}would{\i0} go\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and act on their own!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.27,0:15:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's contact the administrative office.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:15:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Put us through right away. I need\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to speak with Commander Layla.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.61,0:16:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.54,0:16:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is about Yuuki Manabu, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.55,0:16:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes, ma'am. In fact, Louis is with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We haven't been able to contact them,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}nor has there been any report from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.89,0:16:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They are on the {\i1}Eternity{\i0}, which\N{\c&He1e1e1&}ties this world with the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.56,0:16:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It is a special train, which does not\N{\c&He1e1e1&}appear on any timetable or diagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.56,0:16:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There is no way to stop this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.23,0:16:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}B- but what about Manabu and Louis?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.23,0:16:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They acted under their own will.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Leave them to their fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.90,0:16:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I cannot do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.57,0:16:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Follow the threads of destiny.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That is all I can say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.58,0:16:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain! I'm picking up\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something on the orbital radar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.25,0:16:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Display it on the main monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.58,0:16:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it, not again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.59,0:16:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You needn't worry. We'll be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}sure to find your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.60,0:16:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The signal disappeared just ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.93,0:17:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry to the target point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.53,0:17:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Say, Bruce, a thousand ables\N{\c&He1e1e1&}says we'll make it back safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.21,0:17:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you, stupid? If we don't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make it back, you're out either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.54,0:17:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.88,0:17:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.88,0:17:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maximum output! Don't lose\N{\c&He1e1e1&}sight of them, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.89,0:17:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.56,0:17:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.23,0:17:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Output is dropping.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We cannot get any closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.91,0:17:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's go, Karen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.24,0:17:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.24,0:17:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where are you going?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}What station is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hazama Station. We're getting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}tired of riding on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.58,0:17:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.58,0:17:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}My mother is here to pick me up. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:17:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where's Terry?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:17:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where is that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.26,0:18:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you talking about?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry, he's leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.86,0:18:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.86,0:18:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once you pass through here,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you cannot return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Karen, I won't leave you again.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll be with you forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.54,0:18:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.20,0:18:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- You can't go!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.21,0:18:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you here for!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.21,0:18:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you go through that gate,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you'll die, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.58,0:18:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You won't ever be able to come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why are you going to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}throw your life away?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.88,0:18:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're alive, aren't you? What about\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the sister you're leaving behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.55,0:18:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tell Jane that her brother is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.56,0:18:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How selfish of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.22,0:18:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How could you understand?
